C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Grand Teki","CreatedById":177895,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-04T10:16:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh, it\u0027s called a gravity assist!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Regor","CreatedById":175796,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-04T10:17:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI find them extremely hard to do!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Grand Teki","CreatedById":177895,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-04T10:17:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrue...\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Regor","CreatedById":175796,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-04T10:18:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLOL, cant give more rep\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Grand Teki","CreatedById":177895,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-04T10:18:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nrip rep\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wasml","CreatedById":120438,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-04T16:21:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think you\u0027ll need \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/115114-130plugin-sigma-binary-v163/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003ESigma Binary\u003C/a\u003E to get Kerbol/Sun going. The rest should be achievable with some text editing of the config files - in the \u0022Orbit\u0022 section for each of the planets.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-04T16:22:07Z\u0022 title=\u002206/04/2017 04:22  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 4, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by wasml\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DStaal","CreatedById":155685,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-04T20:36:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe one comment I have is that I don\u0027t believe having planets in 180\u02DA opposing orbits actually is stable - it\u0027d be more realistic to have them in trojan orbits to the larger body. \u00A0(So Kerbin would be in one of the Earth-Sun trojans, etc.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wasml","CreatedById":120438,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-04T23:41:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is the L3 point at 180 degrees - Jupiter has some asteroids there - though not sure how long something could be expected to last there. More interesting is the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Co-orbital_configuration\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehorseshoe\u003C/a\u003E orbit - but would need a mod to make planets do that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}